<div><h3>SOC 180 - Aging and Society </h3>  <hr>This course examines the diversity of the elderly in the U.S. and challenges aging as a social problem.  We examine what it means to age successfully and how society can better the lives of its elderly members.  Special attention is paid to income inequality, retirement, social security, and health care.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> VP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every other year<br><br></div>		</td>
